**[1860, 01-12] Ms.A.4.6A.2.12**

James Redpath to MWC; Boston. “I am preparing a volume of the best
utterances called forth by the Invasion of Virginia. Of course, among
them will be the Letter of Victor Hugo.” The autograph of the author is
to follow each item. “I can find none, published, of Victor Hugo. I
infer that you have an original Letter from him.” He asks if she will
permit an engraving of the autograph to be made.


